&lt;p>Stay connected with us on social media:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Understanding Hugo Render Hooks</title><link>/page/render-hooks/</link><pubDate>Mon, 25 Mar 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/page/render-hooks/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="hugo-render-hooks">Hugo Render Hooks&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Render hooks are a powerful feature in Hugo that allows you to customize how different types of content are rendered in your site. This guide will help you understand how to use render hooks effectively.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="what-are-render-hooks">What are Render Hooks?&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Render hooks are templates that Hugo uses to render specific types of content. They allow you to override the default rendering behavior for:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Images&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Links&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Headings&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Code blocks&lt;/li>
&lt;li>And more&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="basic-structure">Basic Structure&lt;/h2>
